  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Comunidad, pertenencia, extrenjer\u00eda,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, explores significant themes around community and belonging. While this scholarly work has yet to generate citations or public mentions, it is firmly anchored in a relevant discourse on sustainability and policy, evidenced by its alignment with one of the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The publication \"Comunidad, pertenencia, extrenjer\u00eda\" serves as an important scholarly contribution to discussions surrounding community identity and belonging, reflecting contemporary social issues. Although the work has not yet received citations, its potential impact lies in its engagement with pertinent themes that intersect academia and public discourse, particularly around the concept of sustainability.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The analytical lens of this work positions it within broader conversations on social belonging, highlighting its relevance to current societal challenges. The commitment to concepts associated with sustainability and policy, evidenced by its alignment with the Sustainable Development Goal framework, indicates the authors' intention to connect academic research with practical applications that resonate in communities.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citations and online mentions, the inferred role of policy relevance signifies that \"Comunidad, pertenencia, extrenjer\u00eda\" may act as a catalyst for discussions in various fields. Its association with commercial platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads also suggests a potential avenue for reaching wider audiences beyond academia, given the book\u2019s content aligns with growing societal interests.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In conclusion, while the immediate academic footprint appears limited, the foundational themes within this publication position it well for future exploration and potential influence. The authors are encouraged to foster discussions surrounding their work to enhance visibility and engagement, solidifying its place in essential conversations about community, belonging, and sustainability.</p>",
